column2:
No.1 Potential causes
A. Potential causes
Air pipe leakage
B. Vehicle / Engine Diagnostic checks
Check air supply line leakage
C. Turbocharger condition and Effects
Overspeed burst compresore wheel, small dent on rear of compressore wheel
D. Recommended Action
Replace or repair leakage from air pipe

No.2 Potential causes
A. Potential causes
Burned Valves
B. Vehicle / Engine Diagnostic checks
Check engine head condition
C. Turbocharger condition and Effects
Turbine wheel shaft BENT, turbine blades burned, over speeding, Excessive temperature (over heating)
D. Recommended Action
Replace or repair engine head valves total failure of turbocharger

No.3 Potential causes
A. Potential causes
Restricted exhaust systems
B. Vehicle / Engine Diagnostic checks
Check for restricted Catalyst converter
C. Turbocharger condition and Effects
Gas leakage from VNT bush, potential VNT vane stick
D. Recommended Action
Replace Coked restricted, catalyst converter

No.4 Potential causes
A. Potential causes
Oil pump malfunction
B. Vehicle / Engine Diagnostic checks
Check engine oil pressure, condition of oil feed pipe
C. Turbocharger condition and Effects
Core assembly journal bearing (bush) get damage, Discolouration of shaft ( Red or Blue)
D. Recommended Action
Repair engine oil filtration system, clean breather system, check for journal bearing rubbed / wheel damage / change turbo or core assembly

No.5 Potential causes
A. Potential causes
Fuel pump malfunction or incorrect fuel timing
B. Vehicle / Engine Diagnostic checks
Check fuel injection system for correct function
C. Turbocharger condition and Effects
Turbine wheel shaft BENT, turbine blades burned, over speeding, Excessive temperature (over heating)
D. Recommended Action
Repair fuel system, check for journal bearing rubbed / wheel damage / change turbo or core assembly, VNT sticking

No.13 Potential causes
A. Potential causes
Lubricating oil contaminated with dirt , sludge, water and non-combusted fuel end up in oil by this dilution
B. Vehicle / Engine Diagnostic checks
Check engine oil /filter condition, service history
C. Turbocharger condition and Effects
Dirty oil causes grooves in journal bearing, Worn piston rings and carbon built up on shaft
D. Recommended Action
Repair engine oil filtration system, change engine oil, clean breather system, check for journal bearing rubbed / wheel damage / change turbo or core assembly

No.14 Potential causes
A. Potential causes
Low quality oil (un branded) oil used
B. Vehicle / Engine Diagnostic checks
Check engine oil /filter condition, service history
C. Turbocharger condition and Effects
Dirty oil causes grooves in journal bearing, Worn piston rings and carbon built up on shaft
D. Recommended Action
Repair engine oil filtration system, change engine oil, clean breather system, check for journal bearing rubbed / wheel damage / change turbo or core assembly

No.15 Potential causes
A. Potential causes

B. Vehicle / Engine Diagnostic checks
Check exhaust system for oil contamination
C. Turbocharger condition and Effects
Tight rotation of chra due to carbon built up, VNT blades get sticking
D. Recommended Action
Run engine under load to clear deposits

C. Turbocharger condition and Effects
Oil leakage from piston ring seal into turbine housings, tight rotation of chra due to carbon built up, VNT blade sticking due to carbon built up
D. Recommended Action
Replace oil drain pipe, check turbo for tight rotation of turbine wheel and VNT sticking
